Description: Poor Naruto: he must cope with a ninja summit and a target on the back of his good friend, Sasuke.
Title: NARUTO, VOL. 49
Author: Masashi Kishimoto

Description: Syaoran faces off against Fei-Wang Reed, a villain willing to destroy the universes to fulfill his desire!
Title: TSUBASA: RESERVOIR CHRONICLE, VOL. 28
Author: Clamp

Description: A young merchant finds himself with a companion: Holo, the Wolf-God of the harvest, and encounter some business opportunities.
Title: SPICE AND WOLF, VOL. 3
Author: Isuna Hasekura and Ju Ayakura
Contributor: by Isuna Hasekura and Ju Ayakura

Description: From the publisher: "Get ready to brush up on world history with these handsome and hysterical personifications of the Axis Powers as they meet, become friends and form one of the most powerful alliances the world has ever seen."
Title: HETALIA AXIS POWERS, VOL. 1
Author: Hidekaz Himaruya

Description: Alice wanders into a very different part of Wonderland in this interpretation of the classic tale. In this new area of the fantasy land, every man is in love with Alice... and firearms.
Title: ALICE IN THE COUNTRY OF HEARTS, VOL. 5
Author: QuinRose

Description: Sebastian is a loyal butler who moves easily from dinner parties to the underworld. Is he too good to be true? Is he even human?
Title: BLACK BUTLER, VOL. 3
Author: Yana Toboso

Description: Yui joins an after–school pop music club with the hope of becoming their lead guitarist before the school festival.  Eat your heart out, Rachel Berry!
Title: K-ON!, VOL. 1
Author: Kakifly

Description: This series is about Misaki, a feminist and the president of the student council... who works at a maid cafe. What will happen when "the sexiest boy at school" finds out?
Title: MAID SAMA!, VOL. 7
Author: Hiro Fujiwara

Description: Isn’t being a kid hard enough? For this group, who are also part bird, nothing comes easy. An F.B.I. agent steps in to help, but the evil "erasers" lurk around the corner.
Title: MAXIMUM RIDE, VOL. 3
Author: James Patterson and NaRae Lee
Contributor: by James Patterson and NaRae Lee

Description: This series is about grade-school boys who want to become professionals in the manga industry. In this installment, they visit a publishing house to pitch their work.
Title: BAKUMAN, VOL. 2
Author: Takeshi Obata and Tsugumi Ohba
Contributor: by Takeshi Obata and Tsugumi Ohba
